The paper discusses automatic annotation of documents with controlled vocabulary terms for document indexing and retrieval, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also presents a statistical, associative system that is trained on texts, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the Semantic Web, which is a topic in both information retrieval and artificial intelligence. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the software according to a human evaluation, which is a common topic in deep learning (cs.DL) and natural language processing.
